  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The main objectives of this study are:&#xD;
&#xD;
        -  To evaluate the driving capacities in a population of elderly subjects with early stage&#xD;
           Alzheimer Disease (AD) in a real-life situation.&#xD;
&#xD;
        -  Define a typology of the main errors made in this population.&#xD;
&#xD;
        -  Propose adaptive measures or technological aids that would make it possible for these&#xD;
           patients to maintain their ability to drive a car while limiting risk.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
